Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and low serum CO₂, suggesting impaired renal function (possible acute or chronic kidney disease) and metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal or hepatic pathology. Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, making diabetes less likely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal and hepatic dysfunction.
